OL,6,FIt was conducted at Ysbyty Glan Clwyd
OL,7,Fby Dr Muhammed Aslam, a consultant
OL,8,Fhistopathologist who proposed that the
OL,9,Fmedical cause of death was acute blood
OL,10,Floss due to an injured abdominal aorta
OL,11,Fwhich had been repaired.
OL,13,FCoroner Mrs Robertson found that
OL,14,Fduring the gastric sleeve operation on
OL,15,FAugust 5, "it appears a major artery
OL,16,Ftrauma occurred. The aorta was
OL,17,Frepaired but she went into arrest."
